From: Mohammed Janahi <MJanahi@airarabia.com>




Dear Team,

    Following the email below, Effective immediately, customers with delaye=
d, lost, or damaged baggage must be referred only to the Baggage Claims des=
k at the arrival airport to file a complaint and create a report.
Please do not raise any new baggage cases on Sprinklr.

Key Points to Remember:

  1.
If the caller says Lost & Found refused to make a PIR, raise the case under=
 Staff Attitude (not Baggage Claim).
  2.
If the caller says Lost & Found is not answering calls for follow-up, raise=
 it under Staff Attitude Complaint.
  3.
Follow-ups should be handled directly between the caller and Lost & Found. =
Kindly advise them to contact Lost & Found politely.
  4.
Lost & Found contact numbers are always listed in the PIR report.
  5.
If a passenger has already reported at Lost & Found but:
     *
Damaged bag complaint exceeds 7 days ( with PIR Report)
     *
Lost bag complaint exceeds 21 days, ( with PIR Report)
then raise a complaint under Baggage Category


Regards,

